  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "There is no problem with insurance at gas stations",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Insurance Association has issued a statement saying that no insurance company has protested regarding the National Fuel License procedure and there will be no cancellation of insurance due to this fuel license.",
        "The Insurance Association of Sri Lanka (IASL) as the body that represents all the institutions in the insurance sector of Sri Lanka confirms that there is no accuracy in the information spread that the insurance will be canceled due to the fuel license. It is further mentioned in the announcement issued by Silva."
      ],
